Text: Now for the finishing strike!
Haaaah!
Aaaagghh!!!

(...Considering this is their first joint attack,
they're surprisingly in sync.)

(The pride of Velgalta's Seven Blades... The pride of
a knight... It's more apparent than I'd expected.)
(But...what will you do now, No. 111?)
It can't be... Lady Karen...
Uh...
Wait, don't tell me...!

(We may have to kill Annerose. It's the worst
possible scenario, but it might be necessaryâ€”)

Have you returned to aid me as a specter...burdened
with grudges?!
(Huhhh?!)
Wha...huh?!
Y-Yes... That's right...!
I...am...a specter...!
(She's actually playing along?!)

I-I cannot die in peace...while I bear this grudge...
So now...I appear before you...as a specter...
Booooo...!

(What a terrible performance! As a former aristocrat,
can't she put on a more convincing act?!)
So it's true then, Lady Karen...! Someone set you up!

(Annerose?! Are you really that gullible? Shouldn't
you be a bit more suspicious?!)

(What even is this turn of events?! It defies all
logic!)
Y-Yes... My family...was murdered...!
Murdered... By who?!
W-Well...!
I-I can't reveal that right now...!

Why?! If you fear retaliation, know that I will never
bow to such threats!

I swear on the name of Velgalta's Seven Blades,
passed down to me from you, that I will uncover
the truth!
Erk!
A name passed down to you...from me...!
(What the heck is going on...?!)

(But...how do I put it? There's something strangely
refreshing about this ridiculous exchange.)

(I don't quite understand, but there's definitely
some sort of shared noble bond between these two.)
Soon...I will reveal to you...the path of truth...!

But you must wait until then... Now, I must leave
this place...!
...I understand, Lady Karen.

I'll wait and see how the investigation goes for a
while. But soon, I'm certain I'll find a clue!
I believe...in you...!
...It fills me with joy...
...knowing you...will carry on...my pride...!
Lady Karen...!

Yes! Leave it all to me, Annerose Nichtsehen, the new
bearer of the title of Velgalta's Seven Blades!
Annerose is gone now.
Hmm. That said, what an incredible performance!
Aaaaggghhhh!!!
What an...utter humiliation!!!

It may have been an emergency, but why did I have to
resort to such a ludicrous performance?!

I'm so embarrassed I could die... Pleeease, just kill
me already!
I get how you feel, but I can't really kill you.

After all, you need to provide intel to Annerose that
will help her act in the Shadow Garden's best
interest. Also...

You need to make sure she inherits what you yearned
for but couldn't attainâ€”the pride of a Velgalta knight.
W-W-Waaah...
We'll need to report this to Lady Gamma as well.

Thanks to your incredible performance, we've set the
stage for Annerose and are now ready to put on the
show we desire.

That's right. All thanks to your incredible
performance!
Stop repeating it! Aaaaaghhh!!!
...I see. One of Gamma's underlings, huh...

Yes, she avoided being detected by pretending to be a
specter while assisting a knight under attack by the
Cult.

Right, a specter... Have you ever seen one,
Zeta?

Well, I've seen a lot of ghost and monster specters,
but none that were human, elf, or therianthrope.
Hmm...

(True, since arriving in this world, I've never seen
a human specter either.)
Hmm...
(Anyway, that aside...)
...A specter, huh...

(She hid her identity, pretended to be a specter,
temporarily allied with the main character to defeat
a common foe, and then mysteriously departed...)

(In other words, she deliberately portrayed herself
as a specter to avoid the spotlight and then departed
while making an even larger impression than the main
character.)
...If they really exist, I'd like to meet one.

(That's a total shadowbroker move! I'm sooo jealous!
I wanna do that, too!)

Because, well, that means even if someone's passed
away, you can be reunited with them again...

(Alright, pretending to be a mysterious specter is
now definitely on my "to-do someday list"!)

...Um, sorry, my lord... I've turned this into a
rather gloomy conversation.
Zeta?

Look at me, talking about specters...and those who've
passed away...

...Still, you listened to me speak...with such
attentiveness and solemnity... Thank you.
...Right.

I also really need to get better at controlling my
emotions.

Emotional fluctuations can get in the way of
completing a mission.
Yeah, that's right.
